            <paragraph>A one-shot timer managed by the scene tree, which emits <reference internal="True" refid="class-scenetreetimer-signal-timeout"><inline classes="std std-ref">timeout</inline></reference> on completion. See also <reference internal="True" refuri="class_scenetree#class-scenetree-method-create-timer"><inline classes="std std-ref">SceneTree.create_timer()</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>As opposed to <reference internal="True" refuri="class_timer#class-timer"><inline classes="std std-ref">Timer</inline></reference>, it does not require the instantiation of a node. Commonly used to create a one-shot delay timer as in the following example:</paragraph>
